**Idea:** Use a sliding window to maintain sum
>**T/S:** O(n)/O(1), where n = size(code), (ignoring space for output)
```
public int[] decrypt(int[] code, int k) {
	var n = code.length;
	return k > 0 
		 ? decrypt(code, new int[n], k, 1, k + 1) 
		 : decrypt(code, new int[n], k, n + k, n);
}

// [left, right)
private int[] decrypt(int[] code, int[] decode, int k, int left, int right) {
	if (k == 0)
		return decode;

	var sum = decode[0] = Arrays.stream(code, left, right).sum();

	for (int i = 1, n = decode.length; i < n; i++, left++, right++)
		decode[i] = sum += code[right % n] - code[left % n];

	return decode;
}
```
