solutions.content:
dp[i] == Number of deletions to balance `str[0, i]`. Also `dp[0] == 0` since it's balanced.
Now if we see an `a` then we have two choices
	- Delete the `a` in which case total steps will be `dp[i-1]+1`
	- Keep the `a` and delete all preceding `b`, in which case dp[i] = `total b count so far`
	- We pick the min of the above two
If we see a `b` then nothing needs to be done as `b` at end is legit. We just update counter for number of seen `b`.
We can make it work with no additional space by just tracking the total deletions so far.

Time `O(N)`
Space `O(1)`



```
class Solution {
    public int minimumDeletions(String s) {
        int totDel = 0, totB = s.charAt(0) == 'b' ? 1 : 0;
        for (int i = 1; i < s.length(); i++) {
            if (s.charAt(i) == 'a') {
                totDel = Math.min(totDel+1, totB);
            } else {
                totB++;
            }
        }
        return totDel;
    }
}
```

